      <description>&lt;p&gt;I’m a Lecturer in Social Policy at the University of Bath. Currently, I’m working on a &lt;a href=&#34;https://helenkowalewska.uk/project/esrc-new-investigators-grant/&#34;&gt;New Investigator Grant&lt;/a&gt; funded by the Economic and Social Research Council, which looks at the relationship between social policies and women’s employment across advanced economies. Prior to this, I held postdoc positions at the University of Oxford and the University of Southampton, where I also received my &lt;a href=&#34;https://eprints.soton.ac.uk/417383/1/Helen_Kowalewska_Minor_Corrections.pdf&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;PhD&lt;/a&gt; in 2018. My research has been published in &lt;a href=&#34;https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/0950017020971221&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Work, Employment &amp;amp; Society&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://journals.sagepub.com/doi/10.1177/0958928716673316&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Journal of European Social Policy&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1017/S0047279419000722&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Journal of Social Policy&lt;/a&gt;, and &lt;a href=&#34;https://doi.org/10.1017/S1474746415000330&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;Social Policy &amp;amp; Society&lt;/a&gt; and has been featured in the media, such as in &lt;a href=&#34;https://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/household-earnings-sole-women-men-gender-us-west-europe-salary-a8894426.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;The Independent&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
